# 🕐 Technician Attendance System — Full Implementation Plan

> **QR-Based Clock In/Out + Shift Tracking + Service Admin Visibility**

---

## 📋 Requirements Summary

The attendance page has **3 core actions** plus an important aggregation rule:

| # | Action | Description |
|---|--------|-------------|
| 1 | **Clock In** | Technician taps → QR scanner opens → scans workshop QR → marked as PRESENT. Service Admin can see. |
| 2 | **Start / End Shift** | Start Shift = actively working (🟢). End Shift = on break/resting (🟡). Can toggle multiple times. |
| 3 | **Clock Out** | Technician taps → QR scanner opens → scans workshop QR → checked out for the day. Admin sees checkout. |
| 4 | **Same-Day Re-entry** | If someone accidentally clocks out and clocks back in on the same day, total hours **accumulate** across all sessions. (1h + 2h = 3h) |

---

## 🔄 State Machine

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NOT_CHECKED_IN
    NOT_CHECKED_IN --> CHECKED_IN_IDLE : Scan QR → Clock In
    CHECKED_IN_IDLE --> SHIFT_ACTIVE : Tap Start Shift
    CHECKED_IN_IDLE --> CHECKED_OUT : Scan QR → Clock Out
    SHIFT_ACTIVE --> SHIFT_PAUSED : Tap End Shift (resting)
    SHIFT_ACTIVE --> CHECKED_OUT : Scan QR → Clock Out (auto-ends shift)
    SHIFT_PAUSED --> SHIFT_ACTIVE : Tap Start Shift (resume)
    SHIFT_PAUSED --> CHECKED_OUT : Scan QR → Clock Out
    CHECKED_OUT --> CHECKED_IN_IDLE : Scan QR → Clock In (same day re-entry)
```

**States explained:**

| State | Mobile UI | Admin Sees |
|-------|-----------|------------|
| `NOT_CHECKED_IN` | Big "Clock In" button + QR icon | ⚫ Offline |
| `CHECKED_IN_IDLE` | "Start Shift" button prominent | 🔵 Checked In (idle) |
| `SHIFT_ACTIVE` | Live timer + "End Shift" button | 🟢 Active (working) |
| `SHIFT_PAUSED` | Break timer + "Start Shift" button | 🟡 On Break |
| `CHECKED_OUT` | Summary card + re-entry option | 🔴 Checked Out |

---

## 🗄️ Phase 1: Database Schema Changes

### 1.1 New Table: `attendance_shifts`

Tracks individual work segments within a single attendance (clock-in) session. Each "Start Shift → End Shift" cycle creates one record.

```sql
-- Migration: create_attendance_shifts_table
CREATE TABLE public.attendance_shifts (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    attendance_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.technician_attendance(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    start_time TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    end_time TIMESTAMPTZ,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_attendance_shifts_attendance_id ON public.attendance_shifts(attendance_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_attendance_shifts_start_time ON public.attendance_shifts(start_time);
```

**Relationships:**
- `technician_attendance` 1 → ∞ `attendance_shifts`
- Each clock-in session can have multiple shift segments

### 1.2 New Table: `workshop_qr_codes`

Stores the QR code secret for each dealer's workshop. The QR code printed/displayed in the workshop contains this secret.

```sql
-- Migration: create_workshop_qr_codes_table
CREATE TABLE public.workshop_qr_codes (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    dealer_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.dealers(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    qr_secret VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    label VARCHAR(100) DEFAULT 'Main Workshop',
    is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
    UNIQUE(dealer_id, qr_secret)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_workshop_qr_dealer ON public.workshop_qr_codes(dealer_id);
```

**QR Code Content Format:** `SUZUKY-WS-{dealer_id}-{qr_secret}`

### 1.3 Modify `technician_attendance` Table

Add a column to record what QR code was scanned (for audit trail):

```sql
-- Migration: add_qr_columns_to_attendance
ALTER TABLE public.technician_attendance 
    ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS clock_in_qr_code VARCHAR(200),
    ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS clock_out_qr_code VARCHAR(200),
    ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS clock_out_gps_lat DECIMAL(10,8),
    ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS clock_out_gps_lng DECIMAL(11,8);
```

### 1.4 Prisma Schema Updates

```prisma
// Add to schema.prisma

model attendance_shifts {
  id            String                @id @default(dbgenerated("gen_random_uuid()")) @db.Uuid
  attendance_id String                @db.Uuid
  start_time    DateTime              @default(now()) @db.Timestamptz(6)
  end_time      DateTime?             @db.Timestamptz(6)
  created_at    DateTime?             @default(now()) @db.Timestamptz(6)
  updated_at    DateTime?             @default(now()) @db.Timestamptz(6)
  technician_attendance technician_attendance @relation(fields: [attendance_id], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@index([attendance_id])
  @@index([start_time])
  @@schema("public")
}

model workshop_qr_codes {
  id         String    @id @default(dbgenerated("gen_random_uuid()")) @db.Uuid
  dealer_id  String    @db.Uuid
  qr_secret  String    @db.VarChar(100)
  label      String?   @default("Main Workshop") @db.VarChar(100)
  is_active  Boolean?  @default(true)
  created_at DateTime? @default(now()) @db.Timestamptz(6)
  updated_at DateTime? @default(now()) @db.Timestamptz(6)
  dealers    dealers   @relation(fields: [dealer_id], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@unique([dealer_id, qr_secret])
  @@index([dealer_id])
  @@schema("public")
}

// Modify technician_attendance model — add:
//   clock_in_qr_code  String?  @db.VarChar(200)
//   clock_out_qr_code String?  @db.VarChar(200)
//   clock_out_gps_lat Decimal? @db.Decimal(10, 8)
//   clock_out_gps_lng Decimal? @db.Decimal(11, 8)
//   attendance_shifts attendance_shifts[]
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Follow the `/prisma-schema-change` workflow for Supabase migrations. Run SQL directly on Supabase, then `npx prisma db pull` to sync.

