## ⏱️ Implementation Order (Recommended)

```
Step 1: Database migrations (15 min)
  → Create tables, alter columns, prisma db pull

Step 2: Backend APIs — Core flow (45 min)
  → Clock-in with QR, Clock-out with QR
  → Start shift, End shift
  → Status endpoint

Step 3: Mobile App — UI (60 min)
  → Types + API methods
  → Rewrite Attendance.tsx
  → QR scanning for both in/out

Step 4: Backend APIs — Admin (30 min)
  → Workshop attendance view
  → QR code management

Step 5: Portal Frontend — Admin (45 min)
  → Attendance dashboard page
  → QR code display/print

Step 6: Realtime events (15 min)
  → Broadcast events on state changes

Step 7: Testing & Polish (30 min)
  → Test all flows
  → Edge cases (same-day re-entry, midnight crossing)
  → Dashboard widget update
```

---

## ⚠️ Edge Cases to Handle

| Case | Solution |
|------|----------|
| Technician forgets to clock out (stale session) | Admin can force-close. Or auto-close at midnight. |
| Same-day re-entry (Rule 4) | Allow new clock-in if previous session has clock_out. Sum all sessions for daily total. |
| QR scan fails on phone | Show manual fallback? Or retry prompt. |
| Midnight crossing (clock in at 11 PM, out at 2 AM) | The attendance record spans the boundary. Stats-by-date uses clock_in date as the "work day". |
| No active shift when clocking out | Auto-close is safe. Just update attendance only. |
| Double-tap Start/End Shift | API-level idempotency: check if shift already active/paused before action. |
| Multiple workshops (different QR codes) | `workshop_qr_codes` supports multiple per dealer. Label identifies which bay/area. |

---

## 🎨 Design Notes for Mobile UI

- **Color scheme:** Keep the existing orange/amber accent colors from the current Attendance page
- **Animations:** Use `framer-motion` for state transitions (the hero card should animate when state changes)
- **Live timer:** Large, mono-spaced font — feels like a stopwatch
- **Status indicators:** Pulsing dot animation for active states
- **QR scanner overlay:** Already exists in [BarcodeScanner.tsx](file:///d:/suzuky/servicestuff/components/BarcodeScanner.tsx) — reuse with different message strings
- **Break indicator:** Show a coffee cup icon + break duration when in RESTING state
- **Timeline:** Vertical timeline with dots and lines connecting events chronologically
